National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: WINCHESTER, VA
Accident Number: BFO88LA044B
Date & Time: 05/01/1988, 1345 EDT
Registration: N4996H
Aircraft: NORTH AMERICAN T-6G
Aircraft Damage: None
Defining Event:
Injuries: 2 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis THE T-6 STRUCK THE C-150 FROM BEHIND WHILE BOTH WERE TAXIING FOR TAKEOFF.
THE C-150 WAS STOPPED AT THE TIME.
THERE WAS AN ANNUAL FLY-IN BEING HELD AT THE ARPT WITH ABOUT 300 ACFT IN ATTENDANCE.
GROUND PERSONNEL WERE DIRECTING GROUND TRAFFIC.
THE T-6 PLT SAID HE WAS MOTIONED FORWARD BY GROUND PERSONNEL WHO HE RELIED ON BECAUSE HE WAS UNABLE TO SEE DIRECTLY AHEAD OF THE NOSE OF HIS ACFT.
HE ALSO SAID THE TAXIWAY WAS TOO NARROW, WITH INADEQUATE CLEARANCE ALONGSIDE IT TO ALLOW HIM TO DO S-TURNS.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: ON GROUND/WATER COLLISION WITH OBJECT Phase of Operation: TAXI - TO TAKEOFF Findings 1.
(F) OBJECT - AIRCRAFT PARKED/STANDING 2.
(C) CLEARANCE - NOT MAINTAINED - PILOT IN COMMAND 3.
(F) ACFT/EQUIP INADEQUATE,VISUAL RESTRICTION 4.
: 5625 lbs Time Since Last Inspection: 59 Hours Engines: 1 Reciprocating Airframe Total Time: 12752 Hours Engine Manufacturer: P&W ELT: Installed, not activated Engine Model/Series: R-1340-AN1 Registered Owner: WARBIRD LEASING INC.
Rated Power: 600 hp Operator: JOHN WW.
